There is also the TurboTax download version that goes for $36 before taxes. You also get to file a maximum of eight tax returns. 

It makes sense to do the former. You save some money and are simply left with a CD that you can use as a drink coaster.

The Peking Duck is well worth a try. The highlight of this dish is the crispy skin of a roasted duck, sliced thinly off, and wrapped with crepe, garnished with spring onion and a "hoisin" based sauce. If you order a whole duck, do ask for extra helping of crepe, as a standard order comes with only 12 crepe pieces which will soon run out.
If you have a group of about 6-8 adults, consider ordering from the set menu. At $98 (mix of meat and seafood dishes) or $108 (seafood dishes), it's good value for money and well worthwhile.

If you want the more authentic Chinese food, look beyond the section with General Tao and orange beef. Eg: Try their pork belly with preserved mustard green (Mei Chai). It's cooked with black sauce and sliced finely. The perfect comfort (and energy) food for a cold winter night (of which there are many in Montreal).

In the same plaza as Lowe's, Dollar Tree and Five Guys. Look for their clearance sections in each department and by the cash registers. Check out their gourmet coffee section (Godiva, Kona, coconut, hazelnut....)

There are a ton of acts, so to save time and to make sure you see your favorite ones: read about each act to determine who you really want to see (http:\/\/torontobuskerfest.com\/performers.php#all) then check what time and day they'll be performing (http:\/\/torontobuskerfest.com\/whatsup_schedule.php). Festival admission is by donation and benefits Epilepsy Toronto. Tips given to the performers go directly to the performers.
In front of Diana's Seafood Delight market.

So convenient! Let's you off right by the doors of the mall. The Gap is the closest to the entrance of the subway station.
You have to ask for their complimentary green tea, even then they only bring you a cup. Only one outlet if you need to charge your phone.

On Danforth between Jones & Broadview. Free admission, free plate smashing booth,   look for the 6'8" Spock impersonator and the snake handlers. Dance in the street to Greek music, ride carnival rides, play  games for as low as 25 cents, and sample some good food at cheap prices (most $1-$6).
Stock up when they have their buy 3 get 3 free sales.
Lunch specials include iced tea or hot green tea. If you want both iced tea and hot green tea it's an additional $3. You can't use the Yelp check in offer if you're getting the lunch\/dinner special.
They have THE best roti! Perfect for sopping up every last bit of sauce left on your place. Comes to you hot and fresh DELISH!
Their coffee is pretty mild, don't forget to add a shot of espresso if you need to stay awake.
Sweet potato fries are a good alternative to regular fries.
Free Wifi. Weak aircon.

Just noticed that they don't have a bird or furry little animal section.

Callaloo patties only available on Fri & Sat

Woo hoo! Open till 3am on Fridays and Saturdays. Don't know if this is just for Summer.

You can use the free WiFi from Pizza Pizza. Overheard one of "Mama's Boys" tell a customer right before closing that they could even call in an order one minute before closing and they will still make their order. Now that's top notch customer service in my book; Mama has trained her boys well!
Weekdays noon - 1pm there's a line up to the door with groups of girls from the nearby school. No more free Wifi, washroom for customers only. They don't do 3D art :-(

Heisei Market is in J-town. Look for the J-town sign between the Toyota and Lexus dealerships. After you park your car, follow the yellow awning until you see the Heisei Market sign, then enter through the door closest to the sign.
They serve regular bakery items as well as well as vegan gluten free ones, if you want to indulge.
Order the veal sandwich or the eggplant Parmesan sandwich with the marinara sauce on the side and don't forget to pile on the toppings. Soooo delicious!
They are in the process of moving so they're closed for business.
Get the Cassava Cake! Rich and decadent.
If you like tropical flavor combos definitely order the roast pork shoulder wrap. Good balance between sweet and spicy.
If you are in a Dollar tree in the U. S.  everything is priced at $1 or less. If you are in a Dollar tree in Canada, everything is priced  at $1.25 or less.
Free WiFi from Lowe's reaches all the way here!
Will be closed Good Friday and Easter Sunday and Canada day.
One of the very few restaurants in the area open on Sundays.
Donair Panzarotti, according to the owner, tastes like a deep fried pizza. Truly a delicious indulgence!
Inside the Petro-Canada gas station convenience store. They have a drive through.
Formerly Downsview Station.
To get between the passenger pick up\/drop off area and the subway\/busses you need to go down one floor.
#2 Samsun Jam Pong (spicy seafood noodle soup) is spicy! Didn't look that spicy in the picture.
October is the season for mums.
Free WiFi that reaches all the way across the parking lot to Dollarama.

Check out their clearance plants. Staff forget to water sometimes and drastically slash prices on dried out, damaged plants. If you're good at spotting salvageable plants, you'll score BIG time. Got a small dark purple cordyline for 50 cents; it looks pretty beat up but there are two babies at the base SCORE!

Visiting hours are flexible and differ from one unit to the next. Contact the specific unit you will be visiting for their hours. Make sure to visit the Max Tannenbaum Healing Garden on the 14th floor.
TONS of butterflies around the first week of October.

Free parking, a public washroom, many benches shaded by towering trees and trails that circle the park. If you love flowers, the best time to come would be during the Spring and Summer months. Since this is a garden park there are a number of restrictions: "dogs, picnics, bicycle riding, any ball activity, Rollerblade and skateboarding are not allowed". PS bring bug spray.
Near the corner of Dundas and Bathurst next to the library. Washrooms available at the community centre or library.

Parking is free but there is a $2 donation for admission. You'll go through a security check point as well, where they'll check purses and backpacks. Reasonable prices for BBQ and other eats, friendly vendors, well organized and clean (volunteers come around to clean up the tables, lots of trash cans scattered about), hand washing stations at both ends of the eating area. Guaranteed good time if you know the ropes.

Scarborough Historical Museum is on site with "pay what you can" policy. Small museum but a good stop if you're already at the park. Knowledgeable staff in period costume. You'll get to see them in action tooling and carving designs in leather, demonstrating how to use vintage toys and baking goods in the antique oven: free samples Hey!
Easier to connect to the McDonald's Wifi

Open later even after the mall closes, lots of seating at this time.

Check their board for their specials and definitely order their cappuccino.
Pretty chopsticks for sale.

Download their free app for a weekly BOGO offer that you can redeemed every Tuesday and Wednesday from 1pm-5pm.
The cutest little cafe in the area.

Look for the blue sign with the lower case cursive "a" and stoplight (it's on the corner of Chipping Rd and Don Mills Rd). You want to park in the parking lot closest to this side. Park in the middle of the parking lot. You'll see the red Baretto sign on the side of the building.
Cheap bahn mi for $3 and less
Great place to pick up items for a gift basket for the tea lover in your life.
Look for the jewelry store on the corner of Gerrard and Yonge, Banh Mi Boys is right next door.

The Old Don Jail has been renovated and converted to the Bridgepoint Administration Building for the Bridgepoint Hospital next door. It's open to the public from Monday to Friday from 9 a.m. - 5 p.m; you can take a free self-guided tour.
Read the reviews to see what's good as far as what to eat. Their breakfast burrito is delicious even without salsa or hot sauce.
Prickly pear iced tea is brewed in house (as well as their lemon iced tea) and served in a chilled glass; very refreshing! They use Kitimai coffees and teas (Fair trade certified).
Drive thru open 24\/7
Their service is lightening fast even when there's a line up. They have Arizona Green tea with ginseng and honey :-D

If you're having a big party and it happens to be on a Sunday, rejoice because 4C Broasters has got you covered. They have a chicken wing special: $24.99+tax for 50 wings (segments), that's around 50 cents per piece!

The wings are decent and have a crunchy coating, pair it with a dip and you're good to go. Much better than their branch on O'Connor.
Across from Five Guys and next to Starbucks. They have no shame and tell their patrons to use the Wifi from Starbucks XD
Get the Cookie Choux a la Creme - cream puff with custard whipped cream filling flavored with real vanilla, you're welcome ;-)

Make sure to check out their secret menu on their website.

More seating in their patio during the warm months; otherwise pretty cramped inside. No drive through.
Adorable decor, Alice in Wonderlandish. Condensed milk toast is delish! Free WiFi.
They have cats up for adoption.
Open 24\/7!

Get the brownie cookie, more cakey than chewy like a brownie. Rich chocolate flavour with just enough sweetness.
Hidden by construction. Go up middle ramp turn right and go all the way to the end, it will be on your left.
It's not on their online menu but their eggplant ensalada is absolutely delicious! Dinakdakan and laing are tasty but watery.
More seating in the back near the washroom. Free WiFi. They don't accept credit cards. Debit purchases under $5 will be charged a 50 cent fee.
Their butter chicken and biryani dishes are good choices. If you like shrimp chips, you'll like their papadum.
You can add protein to your grilled cheese or salad for $4 extra. Free neighborhood parking (see signs for time restriction).
Milk hoppers and samosas are YUMMY!
Their mauby (tree bark) drink tastes like licorice; the owner says it has many health benefits.
On the left side of the plaza as you enter the parking lot. No visible business sign, best to look for their unit - #222.

Tortilla chips are made fresh in house. Winners are anything with shrimp or fish and definitely their sinfully rich caramel flan (they only make it once in a while).

If you go during rush hours, it's every man\/woman for themself. You need to work your way to the counter,  make eye contact with a staff member and tell them your order. Being shy and unassertive will get you ignored.
HUGE portions at cheap prices. Baked fresh in house.
They serve traditional Serbian food.

Karioka (think fried mochi balls) and Turon (with langka\/jackfruit and sweet banana) are made to order. Comes out hot: crispy crunchy on the outside and deliciously soft inside. Siu mai is delicious as well, don't forget to ask for the chili oil.
Don't order food from here, there's always flies in the food case.
Has a Subway.

TIPS:
- Don't order everything at once, otherwise the waiters\/tresses will slow around bringing you the rest of your order.
-Order just enough for everyone to try things out first, that way you're not stuck with lots of uneaten food and get charged extra for the waste.
-Once you know which items you like, ask for another paper menu then order another round.
- Before you finish eating the food that is on your table, order another round. Repeat until you're stuffed.

Free wifi
Chicken wings are made to order. They come right out if the deep fryer juicy and  tender on the inside and crispy on the outside.
Sign up for their email alerts for a BOGO bowl deal and they'll also email you the 12 soups of the day, good if you're a regular customer.
Vanilla Caramel Latte topped with whipped cream and a drizzle of caramel is delish.
Free neighborhood parking and free parking on Scarborough Road on Sundays!
Breakfast sandwiches are delicious; you can add avocado.

Don't let the outside scare you off, looks much better inside.

Nothing with pork here - no carnitas

Choose the garden side salad with vinaigrette dressing as a healthy alternative. Fresh tasting lettuce,  cucumbers,  tomatoes, onions and olives with a yummy dressing.
They're open Thanksgiving Day.
Pork Pinbone Steak Sandwich is hearty and flavorful. Pair it with their daily soup and you'll have yourself a very satisfying lunch.
The minimum amount to use a credit\/debit card is $20 and they charge 25 cents to use a card if your total is below $10. They have an ATM machine by the door.
Order a whole pizza so they can make it fresh.

Ask staff for sample cups and sample BEFORE you buy. Then get a cup on the table to the left of the machines. Fill your cup with what ever flavor(s) you want (you can even swirl two flavors together), put on  your syrups and toppings, bring to staff to weigh, pay per weight, enjoy!
THIS IS SELF SERVE! They are lacking in fresh fruits but I love the popping boba. Free Wifi. Don't come during peak hours if you want to avoid crowds of kids. Great for families.
Open till midnight everyday.
They stock FOCO roasted coconut juice. So much better than regular coconut juice
They're starting their Black Friday sales today! $15.99 for coral frags, saw blue mushrooms and green star polyps.
Do yourself a favor and get the Amarena cherry macaroon and a cup of Sloane's tea SCRUMPTIOUS!
Actual store fits 3 people standing but there's seating right outside for 4.

Free meal if you complete an online survey.
Free WiFi, password zenq2014.

Use the delicious Tingmo to sop up any leftover sauce DELISH!

FYI: the Gyuma is a blood sausage but on the menu there is no indication of that in the description.
Extreme Fries are just taco toppings over fries: cheese, lettuce, onions, tomatoes, sour cream and burrito sauce.

If you're on a budget make you're own crepe which starts at $2.99 then work your way up as you add toppings. Sugar cane juice is pricey and very sweet. Ask for an extra glass of ice then split it into two drinks; hey, two drinks for the price of one!  Free Wifi. Free 20 minute parking out front or you can park in their underground parking if you're planning to eat in.

It is located in an awkward spot. Look for the towering World on Yonge condos, look for the traffic light between Glen Cameron and Meadowview and turn into the parking lot between the World on Yonge condos and the Shops on Yonge plaza. Muncheez will be on your left, on the same side as Love Me Sweet.
$5 kid's meals served Tues-Sat 5pm-7pm. Brunch served Sat & Sun 10-3pm.
Get the Portuguese stew with chorizo and collard greens. Tasty!

Meals come with rice, salad, soup, your choice of mango or pineapple juice, and Somali tea to end your meal. Portions are large. Awesome value!
They'll do a half and half pizza if you ask nicely.
Delicious sandwiches and tea. Traditional Revani cake is sweet but would go perfect with their Turkish coffee.
$4 value meals HEY!

Spacious with lots of comfy armchairs.
Monday early afternoon: crazy line up at the drive through but none inside.

You can get their Horchata Frappuccino with or without caffeine.

They are only open on Wed, Sat and Sun from noon to 6pm. Don't bother knocking on the door just walk through the narrow alley way to the right of the white house with the black and white striped awning.

You can combine the wing flavors - garlic Cajun with lemon pepper was delish! They'll let you sample the sauces as well & you can also add any sauce on the burgers. Fish & chips served only on Wed & Fri.
Call ahead because they frequently run out of items. They no longer serve pineapple curry or orange ginger wing sauces.
They have a stamp card, one stamp per visit.

They'll let you sample the sauces as well & you can also add any sauce on the burgers. Fish & chips served only on Wed & Fri.

Don't forget to ask for the wet wipes.
Pick up a password by the cash register that's good for 3 hours.
Take the escalator to the top and turn right, it's in the corner. Cash only but there's an ATM one floor below besides the escalator.
Free Wifi, open late. Come here if you want a sugar rush.

Lunch specials (not available for delivery) from $6.95-8.95 served between 11am-3pm which comes with rice. Add $3 for a small side salad,  spring roll and drink. Spice levels are higher than other places so beware.
Free Wifi. They have the most uncomfortable chairs and benches! Don't  stay long if you have a bad back.
Afternoon tea $28\/per person and High tea is $38\/pp. Make sure to make reservations and that you get a response. We actually made reservations in person and to scope out the place (Sept 2017)
In the shopping plaza next to Longo's.
As you head south on Midland and pass Silver Star turn into the third drive way. The addresses are located on the top of the buildings. Bahn Mi 24 will be on your right.
They offer one egg option for their Eggs Benedict if you eat like a bird.
Underground parking garage houses photographer Hank O'Neal's work.
Pricing as of Sept 2017: $5.50\/6 and $4\/6 after 5pm for all buns on the white trays. Buns on orange trays are more, price varies.
$5 deal of the day sandwiches and $6 Panini & Soup combos are a steal!
Name of restaurant is in very small letters. Better to look for the store front.
Not on their menu but they do serve hot chocolate (regular and white).
Closed for renovations
Check their Facebook page for their lunch special of the day which changes every day. Definitely sample their wares to determine which items would suit your tastes.
See pic for daily specials.
Make sure to ask for samples of the sauce or rub BEFORE you decide. Seasoned staff (not new hires) are experts in helping you find items that will suit your tastes, let them know what you like.
Hard to see at night. Look for the "88" on the street sign and turn into the parking lot. You'll know you're in the right spot when you see a closed gas station next door.
In the orange pink Madison Properties building. Same building as RBC.
Lunch specials available till 4pm! They start at $6.50 and include a veggie spring roll, rice and bottled water.
The name says "cafe" but there's no type of food served, only coffee and tea.
No where near the quality of Max's in the Philippines. See pics.

This is NOT your typical restaurant. Think of it as a very upscale cafeteria. Also read the reviews and look at the pictures so you have an accurate idea of the type of eatery this is, so as not to come with unrealistic expectations. No menus just point to what you want: most are labeled with name & ingredients.
They close during the Fall\/Winter
Get the Halloumi with garlic aioli. Don't forget to visit both washrooms and push the big button!!!!!
The convenience store is moving out and Caffeine City Bistro is going to have the space all to themselves. So excited for the reno!
Sophia's delicious chili only available on Thursdays. Say yes to the shredded cheddar cheese and sour cream. Not spicy so ask for one of their hot sauces to spice things up.
Their WiFi is up and running. You need a key for the washroom.
They have a new loyalty card: 10 stamps and get a freebie drink.
Art show this Saturday Aug 15 from 7pm-10pm. New Menu coming out in Sept. In the same plaza as No Frills and Toys "R" Us.
The sweetest staff. I just bought an iced coffee but they gave me a Lancaster Butterscotch and caramel candy with my drink.
They're open 24\/7, if the door is locked get the attendants' attention and they'll  unlock the door (only late at night).
Car wash is cheaper if you purchase both gas and the car wash than if you just pay for a car wash alone.
Oh yeah! They now have free WiFi! What a way to welcome 2017 :-D
Front part of the building which houses the jewelry stalls, a make up stall and a Caribbean food stall is open during the week.
Definitely get the ham bone soup entree. It comes with a bowl of rice and 3 sides for $6.95 surprisingly lots of tender meat still left on the bones.

Authentic Burmese food with ingredients shipped all the way from Burma. Don't worry if you don't know what to order; the sweet owner will help you; she'll even adjust the food to your dietary restrictions. N3 Noodle with chicken and E3 Burmese Style Beef Curry are solid choices. Don't forget to use the lime and crushed chili available (mild in spice level but it's really flavourful). Call on the weekends to make sure they're not packed because people come from all over to eat here.
Only 2 free parking spaces in front of restaurant. Paid street parking across the street. Free street parking on Sundays.
They have vegan options that are marked on their paper menu.
Look for the Abitibi Dental Centre sign on the building. Enter at the front door,  go up the stairs then you'll run right into the reception area.
Has the same address as Urban Gardener  but Tuckshop's store front actually faces Edwin Ave.

On the busy corner of Dundas and Yonge in the 10 Dundas East shopping centre that houses the Cineplex. Avoid lunch and dinner rush hours to avoid crowds and have a less rushed experience. Suggest to check out their menu and list of ingredients beforehand so you're prepared to order when you get there. Knowing their system gets you a better pizza and a more pleasant experience.
The kids meal is a good and cheap snack on the go. If you order the lemonade, ask for less ice otherwise you'll get a cupful of ice with a few gulps of lemonade
Has a large seating area inside and a large patio outside. They have a drive through if you you're in a hurry.
You have to wait to be seated. Ask for samples (melted, hot, or buttons of chocolate) before you make your decision.
The mall is open on Mondays but not all of the stores are.
In the back corner of the plaza with Food Basics. Look for the sign in the pic and park in the back lot.
If the lights in the washrooms are off, notify the staff. The light switch is by the cash register :-\/
Taste and sample before you decide.
On the corner of Dawes and Chapman, bottom floor (condos are on top). Renovations set for next year to make it bigger and better.
Connected to Esso Gas station
